         | Upon further increasing of $V_g$ the conduction band in the wide bandgap material may bend so much that for some $x=x_s$ it equals the fermi level: $ E_c (x_s) = E_f $. The voltage that realizes this condiction is called saturation gate voltage V_{g,SAT}. For $V_g > V_{g,SAT}$ a sheet of free carrier is formed in the barrier layer between the gate metallic contact and the 2DEG because $ E_f $ enters the conduction band. This charge accumulation contribute to an additional parisitic channel. In fact, raising $V_g$ leads to a growth of this parasitic charge with no further increase in $n_s$. Therefore, the sheet charge density of the 2DEG has a saturation point $n_{s,SAT}$ it is due to the shielding effect caused by the parasitic channel charge in the barrier layer. To increase $n_{s,SAT}$ dopants concentration ($N_{dop}$) and conduction band discontituity have to be raised. Neglecting constants and further parameters it is valid to state that $n_{s,SAT} \sim N_{dop}$ and $n_{s,SAT} \sim \Delta E_c ^{1/2}$ considering only dominant orders.
